Stellus Capital Investment Corp (NYSE:SCM) Experiences Heavy Trading Volume 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsStellus Capital Investment Corp (NYSE:SCM) Experiences Heavy Trading Volume
July 24, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



106K shares changed hands in the last trading session.  Shares saw a steep increase in trading volume of 186.75% over the normal average daily volume. 
 Here is the rundown on market activity for Stellus Capital Investment Corp (NYSE:SCM).   Director Dean D’angelo purchased 1,500 shares at an average price of $13.33 on Tue the 20th. D’angelo now owns $1,350,622 of stock per an SEC filing yesterday. Robert T. Ladd, President and CEO disclosed the purchase of 7,400 shares. The shares were purchased at an average price of $13.22. The President and CEO now owns $2,870,749 of the stock per the Form 4 SEC filing.
 Director Dean D’angelo acquired 6,500 shares at a price of $13.43 on Tue the 13th. The Director now owns $1,340,609 of the stock as recorded in a recent Form 4 SEC filing.
 Here are a few additional firms who have increased or decreased their stake in (SCM).   Creative Planning grew its ownership by buying 1,000 shares an increase of 400.0% in the quarter. Creative Planning owns 1,250 shares with a value of $17,000. The value of the position overall is up by 325.0%. Next Financial Group, Inc divested its investment by shedding 10,901 shares a decrease of 99.1%. Next Financial Group, Inc claims 99 shares worth $1,000. The total value of its holdings decreased 99.2%.
 Bank Of Montreal /can/ bolstered its stake by buying 177,766 shares an increase of 7,957.3% from 09/30/2016 to 06/30/2017. Bank Of Montreal /can/ currently owns 180,000 shares valued at $2,468,000. The value of the position overall is up by 10,183.3%. Morgan Stanley reduced its holdings by shedding 6,826 shares a decrease of 13.7% as of 03/31/2017. Morgan Stanley now holds 43,033 shares with a value of $626,000. The value of the position overall is up by 4.2%.        Advertisement






  On July 14 the stock rating was downgraded to “Neutral” from “Outperform” and a price target of $11.00 was set in a report issued by Baird. On April 27 analysts at Janney Capital started coverage with an initial rating of “Neutral”.
 On January 20 the company was upgraded from “Neutral” to “Outperform” in a statement from Baird. August 10 investment analysts at Keefe Bruyette & Woods made no change to the company rating of “Outperform” and lowered the price expectation from $14.25 to $13.00.
 Equity analyst Stephens & Co. initiated coverage on SCM setting a rating of “Equal-weight” and setting a price target of $13.00. On March 11 Raymond James held the stock rating at “Outperform” but lowered the price target  to $14.50 from $15.50.
 The company is now up by 0.51 percent from yesterday’s close.  Additionally the company announced a dividend for shareholders payable on Tuesday the 15th of August 2017.  The dividend payment will be $0.340 per share for the quarter or $1.36 on an annualized basis.  This dividend amount will represent a yeild of $10.23.  The ex-dividend date has been established as Wednesday the 28th of June 2017. 
 The stock is trading at $13.81 a tad above the 50 day moving average which is $13.66 and which is just a bit below the 200 day moving average of $13.82.  The 50 day moving average moved up $0.15 and the 200 day average moved down $-0.01. 
 Stellus Capital Investment Corporation, launched on May 18, 2012, is a closed-end, non-diversified management investment company. The Company originates and invests primarily in private middle-market companies through first lien, second lien, unitranche and mezzanine debt financing, with corresponding equity co-investments. The Business’s investment objective is to maximize the total return to its stockholders in the form of current income and capital appreciation..
